SIMPLE: fruitless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fruitless
<hw>Fruit"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Lacking, or not bearing, fruit; barren; destitute of offspring;
<as>as, a <ex>fruitless</ex> tree or shrub; a <ex>fruitless</ex>
marriage.</as></def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Productive of no advantage or good effect; vain;
idle; useless; unprofitable; <as>as, a <ex>fruitless</ex> attempt; a
<ex>fruitless</ex> controversy.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They in mutual accusation spent⟦br⟧
The <qex>fruitless</qex> hours.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Useless; barren; unprofitable; abortive;
ineffectual; vain; idle; profitless. See <er>Useless</er>.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fruit"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fruit"lness*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fruit'y</ent>⟦br⟧
